15/02/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The trade union of Serbia's national air carrier JAT warned on Monday (14 February) that employees would stage a general strike Friday, if the government fails to present a concrete plan to resolve problems at the company by that time. 
Finance Minister Mladan Dinkic has said at least 2,000 employees should be laid off to make the money-losing company more efficient.
In other news Monday, judges in the trial of Slobodan Milosevic warned the defendant that he was wasting time by asking witnesses to answer pointless questions. 
The former Yugoslav president has so far used 28 of the 150 days allocated to the defence phase. 
(Danas - 15/02/05; Reuters - 14/02/05)
